Step-by-Step Execution in Exam
✅ STEP 1 — Create New Project

Open Android Studio → New Project
Select Empty Activity
Name: FragmentLifecycle
Package: com.example.fragmentlifecycle
Language: Java
Min SDK: API 21
Click Finish → Wait for Gradle


✅ STEP 2 — Create fragment_my.xml

Go to: res → layout
Right-click layout → New → Layout Resource File
Name: fragment_my
Root element: type LinearLayout → OK
Paste fragment XML code below


✅ STEP 3 — Create MyFragment.java

Right-click java → com.example.fragmentlifecycle
New → Java Class
Name: MyFragment
Paste MyFragment Java code below


✅ STEP 4 — Edit activity_main.xml

Go to: res → layout → activity_main.xml
Replace everything with main XML code below


✅ STEP 5 — Edit MainActivity.java

Open MainActivity.java → Replace everything with code below


✅ STEP 6 — Run the App

Click Run ▶️ → Select emulator → OK
App opens with fragment visible


✅ STEP 7 — Show Lifecycle in Logcat (MOST IMPORTANT FOR VIVA!)

At bottom of Android Studio → Click "Logcat" tab
In search bar type: FragmentDemo
You will see all lifecycle methods printed in order:

onAttach → onCreate → onCreateView → onActivityCreated → onStart → onResume

Press Home button on emulator → Logcat shows:

onPause → onStop

Return to app → Shows:

onStart → onResume
